documentation.text:
@notice The (older) MamaPut contract gives out a constant number of JOLLOF tokens per block.
 It is the only address with minting rights for JOLLOF.
 The idea for this MamaPut V2 (MCV2) contract is therefore to be the owner of a dummy token
 that is deposited into the MamaPut V1 (MCV1) contract.
 The allocation point for this pool on MCV1 is the total allocation point for all pools that receive double incentives.
@notice Address of MCV1 contract.
@notice Address of JOLLOF contract.
@notice The index of MCV2 master pool in MCV1.
@notice Info of each MCV2 pool.
@notice Address of the LP token for each MCV2 pool.
@notice Address of each `IRewarder` contract in MCV2.
@notice Info of each user that stakes LP tokens.
@dev Total allocation points. Must be the sum of all allocation points in all pools.

setMigrator(address).notice: Set the `migrator` contract. Can only be called by the owner.

updatePool(uint256).notice: Update reward variables of the given pool.

userInfo(uint256,address).notice: Info of each user that stakes LP tokens.

withdrawAndHarvest(uint256,uint256,addre.notice: Withdraw LP tokens from MCV2 and harvest proceeds for transaction sender to `to`.

userdoc.notice: The (older) MamaPut contract gives out a constant number of JOLLOF tokens per block. It is the only address with minting rights for JOLLOF. The idea for this MamaPut V2 (MCV2) contract is therefore to be the owner of a dummy token that is deposited into the MamaPut V1 (MCV1) contract. The allocation point for this pool on MCV1 is the total allocation point for all pools that receive double incentives.
